    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of hackberry native to Mediterranean climates and used as an ornamental elsewhere, having lance-shaped, gray-green leaves and relatively large edible fruit. This plant may have been the Lotus described by ancient writers as sweet and wholesome.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
